The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, January 8, 2007

 Whats on

 Emergency 

 services, like hospitals, blood banks, medicine shops, hearse 

 services, trains and flights, will be outside the purview 

 of the bandh. 

 IT offices and firms will function as usual. 

 Examinations will be held at Calcutta University, Jadavpur 

 University and medical colleges. 

 State buses, trams and Metro Railway will ply as per schedule.

 All state and central government departments will be open. 

 All major marketplaces, shopping complexes and multiplexes 

 have decided to stay open on Monday. The services might be 

 withdrawn depending upon the bandh situation.

 Blessed Teresa of Kolkata by Sunita Kumar will be released 

 by Sharmila Tagore, at Oxford Bookstore, 6.30 pm

 The Calcutta Museum at Town Hall will remain open from 11 

 am to 6 pm. Ticket counter closes at 5 pm. 

 Whats off 

 Taxis, 

 private buses, autorickshaws could stay off the roads. 

 All major art galleries in the city will be closed.

 Academy of Fine Arts will be closed. All art shows and dramas 

 have been postponed.

 Majestic Calcutta, an exhibition of photographs by Jayant 

 Patel, at Victoria Memorial, is likely to remain closed. 

 Milieu, Presidency College Fest, scheduled to have been held 

 on the campus, has been cancelled. The programme has been 

 re-scheduled for Wednesday. 




